    "instruction": "Search trace.csv for traces related to the top candidate components. Specifically: consider any trace row in the incident window 2021-03-23 02:30:00 to 2021-03-23 03:00:00 UTC+8 where cmdb_id is in [Tomcat02, apache01, IG01, Mysql01, Mysql02, Tomcat01, MG01, MG02, Tomcat04] OR trace_name contains any of these component names as a substring. For each distinct (cmdb_id, trace_name) found, compute the global P95 using the full available series (no time filtering), then compute these aggregates within the incident window: points_in_window, breach_count (value > global P95), first_breach_timestamp (earliest breach in window or null), max_value_in_window, p95_threshold, severity_ratio = max_value_in_window / p95_threshold. Return only rows with breach_count > 0, limited to top 20 sorted by first_breach_timestamp ascending (earliest breaches first). Also return the total distinct (cmdb_id, trace_name) pairs scanned and how many had breaches. Keep output tabular and bounded (<=20 rows)."
}

